cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper focuses on natural language processing and information retrieval, which suggests it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of neural network architectures and carefully designed features also suggests it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the release of an open-domain dataset that includes web queries and tables suggests it could also belong to cs.DB (Databases).
